All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
delete_error_controller
This class handles all the actions that occur when a user interacts with the delete_error.fxml file.
errorBoxes
This class places errors for invalid data inputs and actions in the correct location on the UI.
Inhouse
The class Inhouse extends the Part class and has a machineId attribute and associated methods to set and retrieve the machine ID.
inputcheck
This class verifies that the data a user entered is valid, or generates errors notifying whats wrong.
Inventory
This class contains a list of objects generated by Part and Product classes as well as methods to retrieve and manipulate the list.
Main
This class is where the program starts by loading the first FXML file, and contains methods that handle loading different FXML files.
Main_form_controller
This class handles all the actions that occur when a user interacts with the main_form.fxml file.
Outsourced
The class Outsourced extends the Part class and has a Company Name attribute and associated methods to set and retrieve the Company Name.
Part
 
parts_controller
This class handles all the actions that occur when a user interacts with the parts.fxml file.
Product
This class contains a list of parts as well variables that stores additional Product information such as name, price, etc.
product_controller
This class handles all the actions that occur when a user interacts with the products.fxml file.
searching
This class handles finding matching parts and products by using the data entered by user in search bar.
